headline: HashiCorp’s (NASDAQ:HCP) Q3: Beats On Revenue But Large Customer Wins Slow Down
summary: Cloud infrastructure automation platform HashiCorp reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q3 CY2024, with sales up 18.7% year on year to $173.4 million. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.13 per share was significantly above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Women in AI: Tamar Eilam is helping IBM build sustainable computing
summary: To give AI-focused women academics and others their well-deserved — and overdue — time in the spotlight, TechCrunch is launching a series of interviews focusing on remarkable women who’ve contributed to the AI revolution. Tamar Eilam has worked at IBM for the past 24 years.
